article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- — Rob Perry had 17 points in Murray State's 81-59 win over Evansville on Saturday. Perry added six rebounds for the Racers (6-9, 3-1 Missouri Valley Conference). Brian Moore Jr. went 6 of 8 from the field to add 15 points. Jacobi Wood had 14 points and was 4 of 7 shooting, including 3 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 3 from the line. The Purple Aces (10-5, 1-3) were led by Kenny Strawbridge, who posted 12 points. Gage Bobe added 12 points for Evansville. In addition, Yacine Toumi had 10 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
